Police recovered the body of 20-year-old a man on Friday who had drowned during a baptism ceremony in KwaNdengezi, west of Durban. Mduduzi Blose,  a member of the Nazareth Baptist Church, is believed to have fallen 3m from the rocks and into the Umlazi River, before disappearing below the surface on Thursday. Members of Durban Search and Rescue (SAR), Umhlali K9 SAR and Metro Police SAR recovered Blose's body  after police dog Dante indicated the area and  a dive operation was conducted. It is understood that a local pastor had been conducting a baptism ceremony in the river at 4am  when the incident occurred. An inquest docket has been opened and will be investigated by KwaNdengezi police.